"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809846","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-22","<p>Improving social mobility is at the heart of the government’s ambition to make Britain a country that works for everyone. A strong economy means there are more job opportunities and that wages are higher, both of which are vital to improve social mobility. The Autumn Budget committed to tackling poverty, improving skills, and ensuring that every generation can look forward to a better standard of living than the one before.</p><p> </p><p>Since 2010 there are 600,000 fewer people, including 200,000 fewer children, in absolute poverty (before housing costs), and employment has risen to near record levels in the UK, accounting for the bulk of GDP growth over the last seven years. The Autumn Budget announced further action to raise living standards by increasing the National Living Wage and to make progress on delivering the manifesto commitment to raise the personal allowance to £12,500. Furthermore, the Budget announced £406m of investment in skills, with a focus of mathematics and digital skills, thereby helping people obtain the abilities they need to secure better paid and highly skilled jobs.</p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-12-22T12:49:44.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809846/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809846/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809846/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-19","Treasury: Social Mobility","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps his Department has taken to improve social mobility in each of the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","120466"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809847","Wales Office","false","2017-12-21","<p>Many of the levers which affect Social mobility are devolved in Wales and therefore the responsibility of the Welsh Government. However, my office works closely with a variety of Government departments to ensure that action in non-devolved areas fully considers the needs of Wales and helps to improve social mobility across the UK.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2017-12-21T10:44:55.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809847/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809847/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809847/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-12-19","Wales Office: Social Mobility","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what steps his Department has taken to improve social mobility in each of the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","120467"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809848","Department of Health","false","2018-01-08","<p>At a local level, ring fencing has been seen to distort spending, and in line with the Health and Social Care Act 2012 this approach has been replaced by clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) having the autonomy to make decisions about the health services that best meet the health needs of their local population.</p><p>However, the mental health investment standard and NHS England Mental Health Dashboard have been introduced to ensure transparency and accountability and set a requirement for CCGs and specialised commissioning hubs to increase their spend on mental health services by a greater amount than the growth in their programme allocation.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-01-08T17:12:39.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809848/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809848/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809848/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-19","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to oral evidence given by the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Health to the Health Committee's inquiry Child and Adolescent Mental Health Services on 21 November 2017, what the evidential basis is for ring-fences ultimately to become ceilings.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","120468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809849","Department of Health","false","2018-01-08","<p>The Department has not made an assessment of the effectiveness of local authority engagement in the Cheshire and Merseyside Sustainability and Transformation Plan.</p><p> </p><p>Across each borough, local authorities are integral partners in developing place-based integrated health and social care systems to provide joined up, better care and improved outcomes for their populations.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-01-08T16:30:46.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809849/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809849/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809849/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-19","NHS: Reorganisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of local authority engagement in the Cheshire and Merseyside STP.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","120469"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809850","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-29","<p>The UK is committed to the Iran nuclear deal. I made this clear when I met Iranian Prime Minister Rouhani, Foreign Minister Zarif, and other interlocutors in Tehran in early December. The Prime Minister and I have made this clear to our US counterparts, and to Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu. We work closely with the US and our E3/EU partners on Iran.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-12-29T10:35:10.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809850/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809850/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809850/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-19","Iran: Nuclear Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his counterparts in (a) Iran, (b) the United States, (c) Israel, (d) other EU member states and (e) the European External Action Service on continued implementation of the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","120470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809851","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-27","<p>I have provided the number of unfilled cases in my response to Question 120475. The number of overall unfilled bookings is available in the published Criminal Court Statistics at the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-court-statistics-quarterly-july-to-september-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-court-statistics-quarterly-july-to-september-2017</a></p><p> </p><p>Table L1 in Languages interpreter and translation services show the number of unfulfilled requests has continued to decrease since 2013.</p><p> </p><p>The department continues to monitor its language service services contract closely with the suppliers to drive improvements and reduce the cost on the taxpayer.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-12-27T15:33:19.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809851/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809851/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809851/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-19","Courts: Interpreters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate has he made of the number of unfilled cases since the contract to provide interpreters to all courts was contracted out; and if he will make a statement?","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","120471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809852","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-29","<p>I have discussed the Iran nuclear deal with members of Congress by phone and during my visit to the US in November, stressing its vital importance for UK and regional security. I will continue to make clear our commitment to the deal to our US counterparts.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-12-29T10:40:24.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809852/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809852/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809852/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-19","Iran: Nuclear Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs what recent discussions he has had with members of the United States Congress on potential amendments to that country’s Iran Nuclear Agreement Review Act; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","120472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809853","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-27","<p>The Ministry of Justice has two contracts which provide face to face interpreting services to courts and tribunals, Lot 1 (Face to Face, Telephone and Remote Foreign Language Interpreting) and Lot 3 (Face to Face and Remote Non-Spoken Language Interpreting). These contracts began on 31<sup>st</sup> October 2016 and make provision for the Ministry of Justice, her Agencies and Arm’s Length Bodies as well as other organisations such as the Crown Prosecution Service to procure these services.</p><p> </p><p>The spend in the first year of these contracts (31<sup>st</sup> October 2016 – 31<sup>st</sup> October 2017) was as follows, with the spend relating to Her Majesty’s Courts and Tribunals Service bookings broken down by region:</p><p><strong>Lot 1</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>HMCTS Region</p></td><td><p>Spend</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London</p></td><td><p>£11,569,011</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Midlands</p></td><td><p>£4,646,429</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>National Business Centre</p></td><td><p>£416,330</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North East</p></td><td><p>£2,331,041</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North West</p></td><td><p>£2,171,464</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Scotland</p></td><td><p>£439,775</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South East</p></td><td><p>£3,369,445</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South West</p></td><td><p>£896,494</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wales</p></td><td><p>£784,002</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total (HMCTS)</p></td><td><p>£26,623,993</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total (all commissioning bodies)</p></td><td><p>£27,978,803</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>Lot 3</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>HMCTS Region</p></td><td><p>Spend</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London</p></td><td><p>£193,731</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Midlands</p></td><td><p>£122,031</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>National Business Centre</p></td><td><p>£173,418</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North East</p></td><td><p>£116,511</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North West</p></td><td><p>£63,255</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Scotland</p></td><td><p>£9,240</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South East</p></td><td><p>£106,269</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South West</p></td><td><p>£39,675</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wales</p></td><td><p>£31,160</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>West Midlands</p></td><td><p>£380</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total (HMCTS)</p></td><td><p>£855,671</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total (all commissioning bodies)</p></td><td><p>£1,135,167</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-12-27T15:37:41.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809853/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809853/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809853/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-19","Courts: Interpreters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the annual value is of the private contract to provide interpreters to courts in England and Wales; and how much is spend on each region on that contract.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","120473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809854","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-29","<p>The UK is committed to the Iran nuclear deal. It is the only diplomatic way to avoid a nuclear armed Iran. The deal is working; Iran is meeting its nuclear commitments, as confirmed by the International Atomic Energy Agency’s latest report (13 November).</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-12-29T10:45:23.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809854/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809854/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809854/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-19","Iran: Nuclear Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make an assessment of the veracity of claims by the President of the United States on 13 October 2017 that Iran has committed multiple violations of the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action; and what information his Department holds on the nature of such alleged violations.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","120474"
