"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808828","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-22","<p>The UK monitors activity generating impulsive noise from pile driving, seismic surveys, detonation of unexploded ordnance, and some sonar activity via the UK Marine Noise Registry (<a href="https://mnr.jncc.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://mnr.jncc.gov.uk/</a>). To address sources of continuous noise, the UK is establishing a noise monitoring network, consisting of long-term monitoring stations deployed in coastal waters. Starting in 2018, UK agencies will participate in the EU-funded JOMOPANS project to develop joint monitoring in the North Sea.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-12-22T13:23:10.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808828/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808828/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808828/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-18","Noise: Seas and Oceans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to reduce noise pollution in the oceans.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","119937"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808829","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-07","<p>There will be no specific information collected from departments to monitor departments’ take up, as this is a guidance document and has been drafted with the aim of departments learning from each other’s experiences when exiting their major IT contracts by providing case studies and making reference to other useful material, including policy.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-03-07T10:34:36.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808829/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808829/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808829/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-12-18","Government Departments: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to Exiting Major IT Contracts: Guidance for Departments, published in November 2017, what information his Department plans to collect to monitor Departments’ take up of that guidance.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","119938"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808830","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-01-03","<p>We are undertaking a comprehensive programme of work looking at the implications of UK withdrawal from the EU. The Department for Exiting the European Union is working with other Government departments to examine all areas of the UK economy, seeking input from a wide range of stakeholders. This includes extensive diplomatic engagement with EU Member States.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker","119940","2018-01-03T17:48:17.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808830/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808830/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808830/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2017-12-18","UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether his Department has (a) commissioned and (b) holds reports setting out the current economic relationship between the UK and other individual EU member states.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","119939"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808831","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-01-03","<p>We are undertaking a comprehensive programme of work looking at the implications of UK withdrawal from the EU. The Department for Exiting the European Union is working with other Government departments to examine all areas of the UK economy, seeking input from a wide range of stakeholders. This includes extensive diplomatic engagement with EU Member States.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker","119939","2018-01-03T17:48:17.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808831/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808831/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808831/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2017-12-18","UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether his Department has commissioned other government departments to produce reports of the current economic relationship between the UK and individual EU member states.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","119940"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808832","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-21","<p>We are undertaking a comprehensive programme of analytical work to inform negotiations.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is seeking input from a wide range of businesses and industry bodies.</p><p> </p><p>Our department works closely with the Department for Exiting the European Union to ensure that they are informed of our understanding of these issues.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-12-21T10:50:30.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808832/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808832/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808832/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-18","UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department has (a) commissioned and (b) holds reports setting out the current economic relationship between the UK and other individual EU member states.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","119941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808833","Department for International Trade","false","2017-12-28","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union leads on the framing of our future economic relationship with the EU and its member states, and this department works closely on these issues, supporting their comprehensive programme of analytical work to inform negotiations.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-12-28T11:08:36.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808833/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808833/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808833/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-12-18","UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether his Department has (a) commissioned and (b) holds reports setting out the current economic relationship between the UK and other individual EU member states.","false","Biography information for Emma Reynolds","Wolverhampton North East","Emma Reynolds","119942"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808834","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-21","<p>The Treasury engages with a wide variety of organisations to understand policy impacts, including the impact on public health.</p><p> </p><p>Public Health England supports local authorities in commissioning effective alcohol prevention and treatment services by providing bespoke advice on good practice to help them meet the needs of their local population. In addition, the UK Chief Medical Officers have produced new low risk drinking guidelines which provide the public with the latest information about the health risks of different levels and patterns of drinking. The guidelines are available at: <em><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/alcohol-consumption-advice-on-low-risk-drinking" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/alcohol-consumption-advice-on-low-risk-drinking</a></em></p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","119944 ; 119945","2017-12-21T13:35:11.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808834/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808834/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808834/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-18","Alcoholic Drinks: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to paragraph 4.17 of the Autumn Budget 2017, what assessment he has made of the effect of freezing alcohol duties on levels of alcohol consumption.","false","Biography information for Caroline Flint","Don Valley","Caroline Flint","119943"
