"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808908","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-21","<p>It is down to the applicant to determine whether they apply to the Community and Environment Fund or the Business and Local Economy Fund. Detailed guidance on each fund is provided on the Fund website.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-12-21T10:00:27.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808908/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808908/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808908/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-18","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, who is responsible for decisions as to whether an application should be made to the HS2 Community and Environment Fund or the HS2 Business and Local Economy Fund.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","120017"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808909","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-12-22","<p>Ofcom is responsible for<strong> </strong>enforcing spectrum licence obligations and it plans to publish its assessment of whether mobile providers have met their licence obligations once it has assessed their compliance in early 2018.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-12-22T10:11:14.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808909/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808909/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808909/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-12-18","Mobile Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether and how Ofcom’s assessment of whether mobile providers have achieved their 90 per cent target for land mass coverage by the end of 2017 will be made public.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","120018"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808910","Department of Health","false","2017-12-21","<p>No fruitless payments in excess of £30,000 have been made in 2017-18 financial year to date.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-12-21T11:52:30.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808910/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808910/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808910/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-18","Department of Health: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, which fruitless payments in excess of £30,000 his Department has made by (a) recipient of each such payment, (b) purpose of each such payment, (c) value of each such payment and (d) reason that payment was classified as fruitless in the 2017-18 financial year to date.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","120019"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808911","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-20","<p>The government is monitoring the situation with the Forties Pipeline System closely. Energy Minister Richard Harrington has spoken to Ineos and the Department of Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy continues to liaise with industry operators to monitor the situation. Any material economic or fiscal effects would be considered by the Office for Budget Responsibility as part of their next forecasts at Spring Statement.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-12-20T16:41:33.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808911/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808911/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808911/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-18","North Sea Oil: Pipelines","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will estimate the (a) direct and (b) indirect costs to the public purse of the decision by Ineos to invoke a force majeure clause in its contract for the Forties pipeline.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","120020"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808912","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-21","<p>The figures requested form part of the Foreign and Commonwealth Office's annual report submitted to Parliament. To date there have been no fruitless payments for expenditure in the current unaudited 2017-18 financial year.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-12-21T13:35:51.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808912/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808912/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808912/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-18","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, which fruitless payments in excess of £30,000 his Department has made by (a) recipient of each such payment, (b) purpose of each such payment, (c) value of each such payment and (d) reason that payment was classified as fruitless in the 2017-18 financial year to date.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","120021"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808913","Home Office","false","2017-12-21","<p>Figures for 2017-18 will be available once the Home Office’s Annual Report and Accounts are audited by the National Audit Office, and laid before Parliament.</p><p>Here is the link for financial year 16/17 where information on previous losses and special payments can be found</p><p>16-17 Page 88 –<br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/627853/ho_annual_report_and_accounts_2016_2017.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/627853/ho_annual_report_and_accounts_2016_2017.pdf</a></p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2017-12-21T16:11:44.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808913/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808913/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808913/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-18","Home Office: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, which fruitless payments in excess of £30,000 her Department has made by (a) recipient of each such payment, (b) purpose of each such payment, (c) value of each such payment and (d) reason that payment was classified as fruitless in the 2017-18 financial year to date.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","120022"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808914","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-21","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by by right hon. Friend, the Secretary of State for Defence (Gavin Williamson) on 29 November 2017 to Question 115305.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-12-21T15:07:12.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808914/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808914/answer","Hansard Extract Wednesday 29 November 2017, 115305.docx","Hansard Extract Wednesday 29 November 2017, 115305.docx","115305 - WQnA extract on MOD Public Expenditure","115305 - WQnA extract on MOD Public Expenditure","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808914/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-18","Ministry of Defence: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which fruitless payments in excess of £30,000 his Department has made by (a) recipient of each such payment, (b) purpose of each such payment, (c) value of each such payment and (d) reason that payment was classified as fruitless in the 2017-18 financial year to date.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","120023"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808915","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-21","<p>The UK benefits from a diverse source of gas supplies and there are no gas security of supply concerns from Forties being offline. While wholesale gas prices rose initially they have since fallen. Energy suppliers typically buy their energy well in advance, limiting the impact of any temporary rise in prices on consumers.</p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-12-21T15:56:49.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808915/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808915/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808915/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-18","Natural Gas: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the effect on the cost of gas to households in (a) Stockton North, (b) the North East England and (c) the UK of the emergency closure of the Forties pipeline.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","120024"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808916","Department for Education","false","2017-12-21","<p>Fruitless payments are types of losses – e.g. due benefit not received, by the department for money spent.</p><p>I therefore refer the hon. Member for Edinburgh East to the answer I gave to PQ 115308, published on 30 November 2017: <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=115308" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=115308</a>.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-21T17:04:22.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808916/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808916/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808916/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-18","Department for Education: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, which fruitless payments in excess of £30,000 her Department has made by (a) recipient of each such payment, (b) purpose of each such payment, (c) value of each such payment and (d) reason that payment was classified as fruitless in the 2017-18 financial year to date.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","120025"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808917","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-21","<p>The temporary closure of the Forties Pipeline System (FPS) is not expected to have an impact on the numbers of people employed on installations within the UK Continental Shelf. Although the temporary closure will have a short-term impact on production for those assets utilising the FPS, industry is not anticipating any adverse impacts on offshore employment.</p><p>Ministers and the Department are in regular contact with Ineos.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-12-21T15:57:51.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808917/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808917/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808917/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-18","Offshore Industry: Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent assessment he has made of the effect of the emergency closure of the Forties pipeline on employment in continental shelf installations.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","120026"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808918","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-21","<p>Within an Amphibious Task Group, the Landing Platform Helicopter delivers troops ashore by helicopter and landing craft. The Landing Platform Dock provides afloat command and control facilities required to deploy and sustain the Lead Commando Group ashore. Both also fulfill a variety of roles in support of wider Royal Navy operations, from warfighting to humanitarian and disaster relief.</p><p>It was stated in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 that a Queen Elizabeth Class aircraft carrier would be enhanced to support our amphibious capability. Together with the existing amphibious ships of the Royal Navy and the Bay Class ships of the Royal Fleet Auxiliary, this will provide the capability to deploy our amphibious forces and support Royal Navy operations.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-12-21T15:03:38.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808918/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808918/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808918/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-18","Amphibious Vehicles and Helicopter Carriers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the role is of the lading platform (a) helicopter and (b) dock; and what differences to their operability there are when used (i) within and (ii) outwith an amphibious task group.","false","Biography information for Gavin Robinson","Belfast East","Gavin Robinson","120027"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808919","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-01-10","<p>Expenditure for Christmas items such as those listed is taken from locally managed budgets, which are approved by delegated budget holders. All budget holders are reminded of the need to ensure value for money for the taxpayer before committing to any purchase.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2018-01-10T16:10:05.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808919/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808919/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808919/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2017-12-18","Department for Exiting the European Union: Christmas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what estimate his Department has made of the cost to the public purse for Departmental Christmas (a) cards, (b) postage, (c) parties and (d) decorations and trees in 2017.","false","Biography information for Jenny Chapman","Darlington","Jenny Chapman","120028"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808920","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-01-08","<p>We do not hold this information centrally. The Department occupies space in a number of OGD buildings and the way paper is procured varies depending on the building. Wherever possible, Directorates are encouraged to use the centrally managed departmental contract for procuring all stationery, including paper when not supplied as part of the accommodation agreement.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2018-01-08T12:54:13.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808920/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808920/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808920/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2017-12-18","Department for Exiting the European Union: Stationery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, What estimate his Department has made of the cost to the public purse for Departmental paper in (a) 2016-17 and (b) 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Jenny Chapman","Darlington","Jenny Chapman","120029"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808921","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-21","At the Treasury Committee, the Chancellor made a broader point about economy-wide labour productivity. Both the Institute for Fiscal Studies and the Office for Budget Responsibility have suggested that increasing overall employment may have influenced measures of productivity. The Chancellor was not suggesting – and does not believe – that increased participation by people with disabilities has had any negative impact on the economy. There is no evidence of a relationship between aggregate productivity measures and an increase in workforce participation of people with disabilities. It has however helped to increase economic growth and it is something we can be very proud of as a country.<p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-12-21T13:22:30.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808921/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808921/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808921/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-18","Employment: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to his Answer of 12 December 2017 to Question 118240, what the exact  references are from reports by the Office for Budget Responsibility, the Institute for Fiscal Studies and other bodies which provide evidence of a relationship between increased participation in the workforce by disabled people and average productivity or overall productivity measurements.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","120030"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808922","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-21","The Government monitors events in Bahrain closely. We regularly raise human rights concerns with the Bahraini authorities in private and in public and will continue to do so. We encourage the Government of Bahrain to deliver on its international and domestic human rights commitments. We encourage those with concerns about the treatment of prisoners in detention to report these to the relevant human rights oversight bodies.","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-21T14:54:00.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808922/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808922/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808922/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-18","Bahrain: Political Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the treatment of political prisoners in Bahrain; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","120031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808923","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-20","<p>Expenditure on training to maintain or update existing skills, including digital skills, is already tax deductible for self-employed individuals when it is wholly and exclusively for the purposes of the business.</p><p> </p><p>As announced at Autumn Budget 2017, the government will consult in 2018 on extending the scope of tax relief currently available to employees and the self-employed for work-related training costs. This consultation will cover the tax treatment of new skills.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","120033","2017-12-20T17:20:26.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808923/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808923/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808923/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-18","Self-employed: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will establish a new tax allowance covering digital training costs incurred by self-employed businesses.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","120032"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808924","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-20","<p>Expenditure on training to maintain or update existing skills, including digital skills, is already tax deductible for self-employed individuals when it is wholly and exclusively for the purposes of the business.</p><p> </p><p>As announced at Autumn Budget 2017, the government will consult in 2018 on extending the scope of tax relief currently available to employees and the self-employed for work-related training costs. This consultation will cover the tax treatment of new skills.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","120032","2017-12-20T17:20:26.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808924/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808924/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808924/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-18","Self-employed: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will bring forward proposals to allow tax-deductions for training courses for the self-employed that develop (a) digital training and (b) other new skills.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","120033"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808925","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-12-21","<p>I refer the hon member to the Written Ministerial Statement entitled Delivery of Universal Broadband issued on 20th December.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","119930","2017-12-21T16:55:00.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808925/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808925/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808925/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-12-18","Broadband: Universal Service Obligation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, when her Department plans to publish the outcome of its consultation on the broadband universal service obligation.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","120034"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808926","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-21","<p>I can confirm that non-insurance contractual debt freeze and other waiver products sold as part of regulated credit agreements are distinguished in regulatory terms from Payment Protection Insurance (PPI). The Financial Conduct Authority’s 29 August 2019 deadline for making redress claims for mis-sold PPI applies only to claims in relation to PPI.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","120040 ; 120041","2017-12-21T11:12:04.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808926/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808926/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808926/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-18","Credit: Misrepresentation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department, the Financial Conduct Authority or the Financial Ombudsman Service distinguish in regulatory terms between non-insurance contractual debt freeze or waiver products sold as part of regulated credit agreements and Payment Protection Insurance.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","120035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808927","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-21","The regulation of consumer credit is a matter for the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA). Any regulated firms offering contractual debt freeze or waiver products must comply with the FCA’s high-level principles, including treating customers fairly. In particular, the FCA has made it clear that firms developing and selling income and payment protection products must think carefully about how they meet the needs of customers. We have passed the Honourable Gentleman’s question on to the FCA, who will reply directly to him by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","120037","2017-12-21T11:00:39.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808927/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808927/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808927/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-18","Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department or the Financial Conduct Authority has assessed the (a) uptake levels, (b) cancellation rates and (c) successful activation rates of debt freeze or waiver products by consumers who were sold those products alongside credit cards and other credit products.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","120036"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808928","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-21","The regulation of consumer credit is a matter for the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA). Any regulated firms offering contractual debt freeze or waiver products must comply with the FCA’s high-level principles, including treating customers fairly. In particular, the FCA has made it clear that firms developing and selling income and payment protection products must think carefully about how they meet the needs of customers. We have passed the Honourable Gentleman’s question on to the FCA, who will reply directly to him by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","120036","2017-12-21T11:00:39.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808928/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808928/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808928/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-18","Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department or the Financial Conduct Authority has made an assessment of the utility or value-for-money enjoyed by consumers who purchased contractual debt freeze or waiver products alongside credit cards and other credit products.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","120037"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808929","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-22","<p>A temporary repair has been installed to resolve the interruptions to the hot water supply at Keogh Barracks, including a temporary boiler to the main accommodation block.</p><p>A permanent solution has been identified and the newly designed system will be installed in the next financial year.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-12-22T11:49:25.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808929/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808929/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808929/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-18","Keogh Barracks: Water Supply","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department is taking to resolve the frequent interruptions to the hot water supply at Keogh Barracks; what steps have been taken to protect the welfare of Service personnel as a result of the lack of hot water at those barracks; and whether his Department has identified a permanent solution to those interruptions.","false","Biography information for Sir Jeffrey M. Donaldson","Lagan Valley","Sir Jeffrey M. Donaldson","120038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808930","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-21","The Foreign and Commonwealth Office and our Embassy in Bahrain continue to monitor this case, and have attended the court hearings. We plan to continue to do so.","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-21T14:56:43.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808930/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808930/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808930/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-18","Sayed Alwadaei","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether officials in his Department plan to attend the trial of Sayed Nizar Alwadaei in Bahrain on 20 December.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","120039"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808931","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-21","<p>I can confirm that non-insurance contractual debt freeze and other waiver products sold as part of regulated credit agreements are distinguished in regulatory terms from Payment Protection Insurance (PPI). The Financial Conduct Authority’s 29 August 2019 deadline for making redress claims for mis-sold PPI applies only to claims in relation to PPI.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","120035 ; 120041","2017-12-21T11:12:04.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808931/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808931/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808931/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-18","Credit: Misrepresentation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the 29 August 2019 deadline for making redress claims for mis-sold Payment Protection Insurance also applies to non-insurance debt freeze and waiver products.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","120040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808932","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-21","<p>I can confirm that non-insurance contractual debt freeze and other waiver products sold as part of regulated credit agreements are distinguished in regulatory terms from Payment Protection Insurance (PPI). The Financial Conduct Authority’s 29 August 2019 deadline for making redress claims for mis-sold PPI applies only to claims in relation to PPI.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","120035 ; 120040","2017-12-21T11:12:04.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808932/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808932/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808932/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-18","Credit: Misrepresentation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of extending the deadline for claims for the mis-selling of non-insurance debt freeze and waiver products beyond 29 August 2019.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","120041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808933","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-21","<p>The Department does not hold any information on the basis for Northern Rail making a commercial decision to increase the frequency of trains from the current hourly service on the South Fylde line without upgrading the existing single-track line infrastructure as it has been deemed not feasible as outlined in the previous Parliamentary question UIN 118756.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-12-21T10:03:55.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808933/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808933/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808933/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-18","Railways: Fylde","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 11 December 2017 to Question 117958 and to the Answer of 14 December 2017 to Question 118756, what information his Department holds on the basis for Northern Rail making a commercial decision to increase the frequency of trains from the current hourly service on the South Fylde line without upgrading the existing single-track line infrastructure.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","120042"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808934","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-21","<p>The Department for Transport has had no such discussions.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-12-21T07:47:53.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808934/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808934/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808934/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-18","Railways: Fylde","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 14 December 2017 to Question 118759, what discussions his Department has had with local bodies or promoters on the business case for public funding to improve connectivity in Fylde constituency by increasing the frequency of train services on the South Fylde line and installing any necessary supporting infrastructure.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","120043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808935","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-27","<p>Significant progress has been made on developing DFID’s new education policy. Since July, we have reviewed the latest evidence on how to deliver quality education, much of which is funded by DFID. We have also consulted extensively, including engaging with education experts in academia, the public and private sectors, and international organisations. This has enabled evaluation of where DFID can add the most value. We are developing a policy in line with our strengths and expertise. We anticipate the policy will be launched in early 2018.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-27T13:02:27.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808935/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808935/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808935/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-18","Developing Countries: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what progress her Department is making in developing the education strategy discussed in Westminster Hall on 6 July 2017 on global education: G20 summit.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","120044"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808936","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-27","<p>DFID has a dedicated Education Research Team with a £12m per annum portfolio of innovative research on education systems, raising learning outcomes, and learning and skills beyond primary education. This research portfolio has a particular focus on disadvantaged groups and the pursuit of an equitable start to learning for all. Research commissioned through this team, along with the UK Research Community, has ensured that teachers, equity and systems reform are at the centre of DFID’s new education policy.</p><p>DFID has commissioned rigorous reviews of existing evidence and, as a result of the findings, concluded a focus on children with disabilities. For example, one research project, which is funded by DFID through the UK Economic and Social Research Council, investigates different modalities for teaching literacy in deaf communities in India, Ghana and Uganda. Wider inclusion and equity issues are fundamental to all DFID’s education research programmes, and we seek to mainstream them.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-27T13:14:31.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808936/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808936/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808936/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-18","Developing Countries: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether her Department is undertaking research on access to education for disabled children and the supply of teachers to inform its Education Strategy discussed in Westminster Hall on 6 July 2017 in the debate on global education: G20 summit.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","120045"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808937","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-27","<p>DFID is proud to be a strong financer of global education. We have made the largest overall contribution to GPE since 2003, and our future investment in GPE will be a crucial part of achieving our new policy objectives. DFID maintains a close working relationship with GPE and currently funds 15% of GPE operations. The UK has been working with GPE through its Executive Board so that it has a compelling case for investment. The UK fully supports a successful replenishment. I am unable to comment on what the UK will contribute at this time, officials are in the process of advising ministers.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-27T13:05:08.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808937/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808937/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808937/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-18","Global Partnership for Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will maintain the current level of funding for the Global Partnership for Education at the 2018 Replenishment Conference.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","120046"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808938","HM Treasury","true","2017-12-21","<p>Between September 2016 and 30 November 2017, HMRC has issued <ins class="ministerial">862</ins> <del class="ministerial">657</del> notices to online marketplaces. In all cases the online marketplace has removed the non-compliant overseas seller from its platform.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-12-21T14:55:22.34Z","2018-02-05T10:20:34.91Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808938/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808938/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808938/answer","Central Devon","Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808938/answer/previousversion/31892","Biography information for Mel Stride","14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-18","Electronic Commerce: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many joint and several liability notices HMRC has issued to online marketplaces due to overseas sellers failing to meet UK VAT requirements since September 2016.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","120047"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808939","HM Treasury","true","2017-12-21","<p>HMRC cannot comment on the affairs of individual taxpayers, as it has a duty to maintain taxpayer confidentiality.</p><p> </p><p>However, between September 2016 and 30 November 2017, HMRC has issued <ins class="ministerial">862</ins> <del class="ministerial">657</del> notices to online marketplaces making them jointly and severally liable for future VAT evasion by non-compliant overseas sellers. In all cases the online marketplace has removed the seller from its platform.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-12-21T14:56:47.023Z","2018-02-05T10:20:13.397Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808939/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808939/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808939/answer","Central Devon","Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808939/answer/previousversion/31894","Biography information for Mel Stride","14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-18","Electronic Commerce: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will set out every enforcement action taken against online marketplaces that have been issued with a joint and several liability notice due to overseas sellers failing to meet UK VAT requirements since September 2016.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","120048"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808940","HM Treasury","true","2017-12-21","<p>HMRC cannot comment on the affairs of individual taxpayers, as it has a duty to maintain taxpayer confidentiality.</p><p> </p><p>However, between September 2016 and 30 November 2017, HMRC has issued <ins class="ministerial">862</ins> <del class="ministerial">657</del> notices to online marketplaces. In all cases the online marketplace has removed the non-compliant overseas seller from its platform.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-12-21T14:53:31.207Z","2018-02-05T10:20:25.277Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808940/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808940/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808940/answer","Central Devon","Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808940/answer/previousversion/31890","Biography information for Mel Stride","14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-18","Electronic Commerce: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will set out every online marketplace that has been issued with a joint and several liability notice and the number of notices issued to each of those online marketplaces due to overseas sellers failing to meet UK VAT requirements since September 2016.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","120049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808941","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-21","<p>The establishment and current strength of the infantry cap badge personnel at regimental duty within the Public Duties Incremental Companies as at 1 October 2017 is given below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Regiment</p></td><td><p>Establishment</p></td><td><p>Strength</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Nijmegen Company, Grenadier Guards</p></td><td><p>93</p></td><td><p>90</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>7 Company, Coldstream Guards</p></td><td><p>93</p></td><td><p>100</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>F Company, Scots Guards</p></td><td><p>93</p></td><td><p>90</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Balaklava Company, Royal Regiment of Scotland</p></td><td><p>99</p></td><td><p>90</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><ol><li>The establishment data is a single service estimate and reflects the role of the units as under Army 2020.</li><li>Current strengths have been provided by Defence Statistics and have been rounded to 10 for presentational purposes; numbers ending in &quot;5&quot; have been rounded to the nearest multiple of 20 to prevent systematic bias.</li><li>Regimental duty is defined as personnel serving in a regimental unit.</li><li>Establishment and strength data do not include attached personnel from other arms and corps. Nor do they include personnel at extra regimental employment in posts away from their parent unit.</li></ol><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-12-21T15:05:32.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808941/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808941/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808941/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-18","Army","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the (a) establishment and (b) strength is of the Public Duties Incremental Companies.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","120050"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808942","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-21","<p>Govia Thameslink Railway (GTR) reports cancellation information to the Department at franchise level. Additionally, the rail industry systems which capture disruption data do not differentiate between cancellations as a result of lack of train crew and other causes attributed to train crew (for example operational reasons). The percentage of all GTR’s cancellations attributed to train crew issues over the past two years is 38%.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-12-21T07:52:16.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808942/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808942/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808942/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-18","Southern: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what percentage of cancellations on Southern on the Brighton mainline in the last two years has been due to lack of train crew.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","120051"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808943","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-21","<p>We are working with Network Rail to provide additional infrastructure, including a bay platform and approximately two kilometres of new track, at Stevenage station to accommodate services between Stevenage and Hertford. Our intent is for this work to be completed as soon as possible in Control Period 6 (2019-24).</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-12-21T11:36:10.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808943/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808943/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808943/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-18","Railway Stations: Stevenage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what his policy is on the provision of an additional bay platform at Stevenage station to accommodate services from Stevenage to Hertford.","false","Biography information for Bim Afolami","Hitchin and Harpenden","Bim Afolami","120052"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808944","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-21","<p>DWP currently operates a number of award schemes; end of year performance awards and in-year reward and recognition.</p><p> </p><p>A total of £41.8m, which is less than 2% of the overall DWP annual pay bill, has been paid between January 2017 and November 2017, this breaks down as follows:</p><p> </p><ul><li>£37.4m - End of Year Performance Awards.</li><li>£4.4m – In Year Reward and Recognition</li></ul>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-12-21T11:04:35.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808944/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808944/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808944/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-18","Department for Work and Pensions: Incentives","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will set out the total sum disbursed on bonuses to staff in his Department in 2017.","false","Biography information for Dr Philippa Whitford","Central Ayrshire","Dr Philippa Whitford","120053"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808945","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-12-21","<p>Proposals are being developed to extend the definition of a ‘position of trust’ in the Sexual Offences Act 2003, to bring into that definition sports coaches who hold a position of trust in relation to a child aged 16 or 17 under their care. We are working to finalise our proposals in early 2018 and will have a clearer view of timing once we have done so.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-12-21T11:02:28.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808945/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808945/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808945/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-12-18","Sports: Offences against Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 7 December 2017 to Question 116539, on Offences against children: sports, when the Government plans to extend the definition of a position of trust to include sports coaches.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","120054"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808947","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-21","<p>DWP does not record the number of medical documents reported as missing which relate to claims for benefits.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-12-21T11:02:10.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808947/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808947/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808947/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-18","Social Security Benefits: Medical Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claimants' medical documents submitted to his Department are known to be missing which relate to claims for (a) employment support allowance, (b)  personal independence payment, (c) universal credit work capability assessments and (d) disability living allowance.","false","Biography information for Holly Lynch","Halifax","Holly Lynch","120056"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808948","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-21","<p>The move of 1 ISR Squadron, including Crossbow Flight, from RAF Marham to RAF Wyton was completed in April 2017. There are no plans to move 1 ISR Wing Headquarters from RAF Waddington.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-12-21T14:59:12.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808948/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808948/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808948/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-18","Air Force: Military Intelligence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which elements of 1 ISR Wing will be relocating from RAF Waddington to RAF Wyton; when that relocation is planned to take place; whether 1 ISR Wing will remain headquartered at RAF Waddington after that relocation; whether the Crossbow capability will remain located at RAF Marham; and when any outstanding decisions on those matters will be taken and made publicly available.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","120057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808949","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-20","<p>The Government has firmly committed to protect workers’ rights, and the Withdrawal Bill will ensure that EU-derived employment rights, including those under the Working Time Regulations, will continue to be in force via domestic law after the UK has left the EU. On 11 December 2017, the Government published draft statutory instruments to illustrate how the proposed amendments will ensure the legal framework that provides for employment rights continues to operate effectively after exiting the EU.</p><p> </p><p>The draft statutory instruments and an accompanying explanatory note can be found by searching ‘Withdrawal Bill’ on the Gov.uk website.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-12-20T12:51:56.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808949/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808949/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808949/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-18","Working Hours: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the future operation of the Working Time Directive in the UK after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","120058"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808950","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-21","<p>Universal Credit provides us with the opportunity to support people to progress, and we are building the evidence about what works, most substantially through a large-scale Randomised Control Trial (RCT).</p><p> </p><p>This trial tests different degrees of in-work support and conditionality by supporting people to progress by providing work coach support and setting mandatory requirements to make sure that individuals take reasonable action that should help them to earn more where appropriate.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The following link provides figures for the data collected so far on sanctions for in work claimants.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/in-work-progression-trial-update-april-2015-to-october-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/in-work-progression-trial-update-april-2015-to-october-2016</a></p><p> </p><p>This showed that up to November 2016, 319 sanctions had been applied to 15,455 trial participants, approximately 2%.</p><p> </p><p>Further statistical information regarding the number of sanctions and suspensions for in-work claimants within the randomised control trial cannot be provided until they are published in summer 2018.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-12-21T11:56:31.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808950/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808950/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808950/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-18","Universal Credit: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many in-work claimants have experienced a (a) sanction and (b) suspension of their universal credit claim by length of sanction and suspension in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","120059"
