"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808995","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-21","<p>We will be launching a consultation on proposals in the Domestic Violence and Abuse Bill and accompanying non-legislative package in the new year.</p><p> </p><p>As announced in the Queen’s Speech this will include proposals to ensure that if abusive behaviour involves a child, then the court can hand down a sentence that reflects the devastating life-long impact that abuse has on the child. We have been working across Government to ensure the consultation addresses how we can best protect and support all victims of domestic abuse, including children who witness it.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-12-21T15:33:04.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808995/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808995/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/808995/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-18","Domestic Abuse: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the timetable is for the publication of the consultation on a Domestic Violence and Abuse Bill; and what steps his Department is taking to ensure that measure for the support of children who have witnessed domestic violence and abuse is included within that consultation.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","120104"
