"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809085","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2018-01-03","<p>At present the Government Legal Department (GLD) provides around 40 lawyers in its Division advising the Department for Exiting the European Union. They have a wide variety of experience gained across government, regulators and in the private sector including in the areas of state aid and competition law. As part of the GLD, they can also draw on the expertise of barristers and solicitors working in various government departments and public bodies including the lawyers at the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy who are the general lead for government on these topics.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2018-01-03T18:32:28.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809085/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809085/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809085/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-12-18","Department for Exiting the European Union: Legal Profession","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what the level of legal expertise on state aid and competition law is in his Department .","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","120194"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809086","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-01-09","<p>The Government is aware that the EU negotiating mandate explicitly refers to state aid and competition in the context of any future trade agreement between the EU and UK. This future relationship is subject to negotiation. While the Government cannot speculate on outcomes at this stage, any future regime will be on the principles of open markets and fair competition.</p><p><br>As the Prime Minister made clear in her speech in Florence the UK shares with the EU “the same set of fundamental beliefs; a belief in free trade, rigorous and fair competition, strong consumer rights, and that trying to beat other countries’ industries by unfairly subsidising one’s own is a serious mistake.”</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2018-01-09T15:55:39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809086/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809086/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809086/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2017-12-18","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether he plans for a new regime for state aid and competition rules to be covered by a future deal between the UK and the EU.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","120195"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809087","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-12-21","The right to data portability is an important provision of GDPR, and we are working to assess the role that government should take in ensuring that it works for businesses and consumers.<p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-12-21T16:21:42.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809087/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809087/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809087/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-12-18","Personal Records: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what steps she is taking to promote the portability of personal data between different digital platforms.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","120196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809088","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-22","<p>The Government is working closely with the Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) to understand the implications on its work of the UK leaving the EU. The Government will continue to work with the CMA on this as the negotiations with the EU proceed.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-12-22T10:36:10.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809088/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809088/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809088/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-18","Competition and Markets Authority","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the potential quantum for changes in the workload of the Competition and Markets Authority after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","120197"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809089","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-01-09","<p>All departments are equipping themselves with the resources they need to get the best deal for the UK. The Department for Exiting the European Union is a fast-paced, dynamic Department at the heart of Whitehall leading on one of the biggest issues for this Government. It attracts the brightest and the best from across the Civil Service.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>We regularly review headcount to ensure we are appropriately staffed to deal with all aspects of our preparations for leaving the EU. The Department for Exiting the European Union now has over 600 staff based in the UK plus the expertise of over 120 officials in Brussels.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>DExEU staff range from policy advisors to lawyers and economists, and have come from a range of backgrounds with experience in vital fields relevant to our exit from the EU, including competition policy.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2018-01-09T12:36:19.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809089/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809089/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809089/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2017-12-18","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what recent assessment he has made of the adequacy of levels of expertise in respect of competition policy in officials engaged in negotiating the deal between the UK and the EU.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","120198"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809090","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-21","<p>Officials in my Department always work closely together to ensure advice is consistent.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2017-12-21T15:48:31.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809090/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809090/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809090/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-18","Council Tax: Dorset","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he has taken to ensure that the advice given to the hon. Member for Christchurch by his officials on 7 November 2017 about council tax equalisation and harmonisation is consistent with advice given by his officials to local government officers in Dorset.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","120199"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809091","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-21","<p>The Government legislated to cap exit payments across the public sector to a maximum of £95,000 and it is intended to consult on arrangements to implement this in 2018.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2017-12-21T15:48:56.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809091/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809091/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809091/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-18","Local Government: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will advise local authorities considering local government reorganisation that no exit payments for local government officers resulting from any such reorganisation should exceed £95,000; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","120200"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809092","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-21","<p>Dorset councils made their request orally.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2017-12-21T15:47:33.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809092/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809092/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809092/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-18","Council Tax: Dorset","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answers of 18 December 2017 to Questions 119513 and 119514, on council tax: Dorset, on what dates officials of his Department received the request from Dorset Council; and if he will place a copy of that request in the Library.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","120201"
